http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/telangana/Students-take-part-in-3K-run/article13987665.ece

Students from various colleges in town took part in the 3K run organised by Swami Vivekananda Utsava Samithi here on Thursday. According to a press release, the run was organised in connection with Swami Vivekananda Jayanti and 125th birth anniversary celebrations of Dr. B.R. Ambedkar.Two-town Central Inspector Srinivas Reddy flagged off the run at Sardar Patel Stadium here. It culminated in a meeting at Pavilion grounds near the bus station.Speaking at the meeting held in this connection, the organisers said the 3K run was conducted to promote leadership qualities and team spirit among youth enabling them to channelise their energy towards nation building.Samajika Samarasata Vedika State convener A. Prasad, BJP district president K. Sridhar Reddy and others spoke on the occasion.